SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 866
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Tyrell Miles, 2024
TSSAA Division I, Class AA Boys' Track and
Field Triple Jump State Champion.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to specially honor and commend those successful athletes
who, through their magnificent exploits, have brought honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable athlete is Tyrell Miles, who, as a student at Claiborne
High School, won the 2024 TSSAA Division I, Class AA Boys' Track and Field Triple Jump State
Championship; and
WHEREAS, a native of New Tazewell, Mr. Miles joined the track and field team at
Lincoln Memorial University as a freshman for the 2024-2025 season, where he continued to
excel and proved himself an important member of the school's athletic community; and
WHEREAS, individuals such as Tyrell Miles are exemplars of the hardworking,
dedicated, and talented young people of our State; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Miles's noteworthy athletic achievements have been a tremendous
source of pride for his family, his alma mater, and his community; and
WHEREAS, his dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect, admiration,
and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Tyrell Miles on winning
the 2024 TSSAA Division I, Class AA Boys' Track and Field Triple Jump State Championship
and extend to him our best wishes for much continued success.
